titleStmt.title:
The Senior Deputy Director General of UNRRA (
                        Jackson
                    ) to the Director General of UNRRA (
                        Lehman
                    )

div.head:
The Senior Deputy Director General of UNRRA (
    Jackson
) to the Director General of UNRRA (
    Lehman
)

div.p:
6. If the analysis above is agreed, it will be necessary for you to take the matter up with the State Department and the President and also, we suggest, with the British Minister of StatePhilip J. Noel-Baker who was attending the First Session of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations, held at Quebec from October 16 to November 1, 1945. who is, we understand, in North America in connection with F.A.O., and the British and Canadian Embassies. It will also be necessary for Gale to report personally on the situation to the Foreign Secretary on his
return to London, and to stress the urgency of immediate and realistic action. We believe that in these approaches to the United States, British and Canadian Governments, we should emphasize that action on the lines of paragraph 4 and 5 above is necessary:— (a)
if Greece is not to go into chaos and (b)
if UNRRA is not to fail
